So this was a bizarre exercise in just reshuffling of 2015 entries. The only addition is Budgie which pushed LXQt down to 20th. I've not done any
proper analysis but it looks like it was the same situation in 2016 too. It would seem that even though our preferences change they're just
changing between the same subset of options.
One notable difference though is the slight shift in favour of DEs over WMs by a couple of %. I find this funny because recently we've had an
increase in posts of WM setups and people complaining about that. People: if you want to see DE posts, make DE posts. There's clearly enough
Window Chef (4), swm (3), and then IceWM, Compiz,
Qtile, CDE, jwm, Emerald, and Pixel all with 2. There
are an additional 33 with one each: check GitHub!
